What is a server:
A server is a computer program that provides functionality for other programs called clients.

What is the role of the domain name:
The role of the domain name is acting as a unique address of the website.

What is the type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com:
The type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com is a CNAME record

What is the role of the web server:
The role of the web server is receiving requests via HTTP and accepting the request when it reaches the correct web server and then sending it back to the HTTP.

What is the role of the application server:
The application server is serving as a GUI(graphical user interface) to the web server which provides the client access to application programs for business logic.

What is the role of the database:
The database is serving as a structure for organizing data or information from the application server.

What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website
The server is using HTTPS to communitcate with the user requesting the website.

Issues with the infastructure:

- SPOF:
The SPOF(single point of failure) in the infastruture is that its is running a single server and this can be avoided by ensuring high availability cluster for the server with a load balancer and providing spare servers.

- Downtime when maintenance needed:
Downtime when maintainance needed like deploying new code web server needs to be restarted : in solving this downtime all we have to do is to update the system and the site and also tesing the patches.
